16 whom a new birth certificate was established pursuant to paragraph (1) of subsection (a)
17 of this Code section may request and receive a copy of his or her original birth certificate
18 by complying with the provisions of this subsection. The state registrar shall require a
19 person seeking an original birth certificate to pay the fee for a birth certificate as
20 prescribed pursuant to Code Section 31-10-27. The copy of the original birth certificate
21 shall be in a form that clearly indicates it is not a certified copy and that it may not be
22 used for legal purposes.
23 (2) If the person who was born in this state and for whom a new birth certificate was
24 established pursuant to paragraph (1) of subsection (a) of this Code section is deceased,
25 any parent, sibling, or descendant of that person may receive a copy of the decedent's
26 original birth certificate pursuant to the procedures contained in this subsection.
27 (3) This subsection shall apply to all applications for original birth certificates for
28 adopted persons presented to the state registrar on or after July 1, 2025."
29 SECTION 3.
